Inner join will only give you rows that exist in the two datasets. What you want here is to keep all rows from the `dataSetTableLeft` and retrieve `label` value from `dataSetTableRight` when `time` matches. 

For this, simply use left join and [`coalesce`][1] function to get `label` value from the second dataset when there is a match. 

Here&#39;s complete working example with the provided data: 

```java
import static org.apache.spark.sql.functions.*;

dataSetTableLeft.show();
//+----------+-----+
//|      time|label|
//+----------+-----+
//|1637020800|    0|
//|1637107200|    0|
//|1637193600|    0|
//|1637280000|    0|
//|1637366400|    0|
//|1637452800|    0|
//+----------+-----+

dataSetTableRight.show();
//+----------+-----+
//|      time|label|
//+----------+-----+
//|1637193600|    1|
//|1637280000|    2|
//|1637366400|    1|
//+----------+-----+


dataSetTableLeft.alias(&quot;df1&quot;).join(
        dataSetTableRight.alias(&quot;df2&quot;),
        dataSetTableLeft.col(&quot;time&quot;).equalTo(dataSetTableRight.col(&quot;time&quot;)),
        &quot;left_outer&quot;
).select(
        dataSetTableLeft.col(&quot;time&quot;),
        expr(&quot;coalesce(df2.label, df1.label)&quot;).alias(&quot;label&quot;)
).show();

//+----------+-----+
//|      time|label|
//+----------+-----+
//|1637020800|    0|
//|1637107200|    0|
//|1637193600|    1|
//|1637280000|    2|
//|1637366400|    1|
//|1637452800|    0|
//+----------+-----+
```


  [1]: https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/api/java/org/apache/spark/sql/functions.html#coalesce-org.apache.spark.sql.Column...-

