Most likely scenario would be a class mismatch.
You mentioned that you are using a `SelectorComposer&lt;Window&gt;`.
That would only work if your declaration is on a Window component like (in zul file):

    &lt;zk&gt;
        &lt;window apply=&quot;foo.bar.MyComposer&quot;&gt;
        ...
        &lt;/window&gt;
    &lt;/zk&gt;

If your composer is applied to anything else (like a div component), then you will receive some sort of failed to cast exception.
For example, if you have something like:

    &lt;zk&gt;
        &lt;div apply=&quot;foo.bar.MyComposer&quot;&gt;
        ...
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/zk&gt;

If that&#39;s the case, you can try using a different type instead of Window for the `SelectorComposer&lt;Type&gt;` to match your host component. If you want something generic, you can use the org.zkoss.zk.ui.Component Interface.

    import org.zkoss.zk.ui.Component;
    ...
    MyComposer extends SelectorComposer&lt;Component&gt;

You should have an error message somewhere with a stacktrace. Most likely in your java console, but could be in your container&#39;s logs.
Please try to find that, and add it to the thread, as this will likely show the actual cause of the issue (in case I&#39;m not quite right on the issue :D )

